  "text": "For the core broadcast protocol [CITATION_1] , the cores are determined in a distributed way. One possible set of cores is {3, 4, 6, 7, 9}. Each core computes its forward node set independently. Nodes 2 and 8 will be included in the forward node sets of nodes 3 and 7, respectively. While node 1 is the source, nodes 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8 and 9 need to forward the packet.",
